----------------------------------------------------------------------
Modifications made in MiniClarc
----------------------------------------------------------------------

The following sections of the upstream codebase have been modified or
extended. See the git log for the full per-commit history; this NOTICE
summarises the cumulative delta as of the listed release.

Release: MiniClarc 2.0.0
Base upstream commit: 62ce78e (feat/auto-approve-in-project-root)

(1) On-request auto-approval (carried from upstream PR #16)
    - Auto-approve Edit / Write / MultiEdit tool calls whose target path
      is lexically inside the registered project root.
    - 16 additional read-only Bash commands added to the safety whitelist.
    - New ClarcCore helper `PathContainment.isInside(parent:child:)`.

(2) i18n fixes
    - PermissionModal "Auto-deny in M:SS" countdown now respects the
      system language (was hardcoded English).
    - Settings → Permission Auto-Deny descriptions localized.
    - ChatKit MessageListView / phase-collapse strings added to en,
      zh-Hans, and ko Localizable.strings (ko had them already).

(3) PermissionMode.fullAccess
    - New case in `PermissionMode` enum (raw value "fullAccess", maps
      to bypassPermissions at the wire level).
    - CliSurface emits --permission-mode bypassPermissions plus
      --allowedTools "*" when fullAccess is selected.
    - Added "Full Access" / "完全授权" / "전체 권한" picker option to the
      permission-mode menu.

(4) Phase-based auto-collapse (chat UX)
    - New ClarcCore enum `StreamPhase` (thinking / text / toolUse /
      toolResult).
    - SessionStreamState.currentPhase updated at every
      content_block_start in AppState.handlePartialEvent.
    - ChatMessage.completedPhase stamped at finalizeStreamSession.
    - MessageListView's groupMessages function extended with a phase
      accumulator; non-text completed phases collapse to single-line
      summaries via the new PhaseGroupSummaryView.
    - Text and error messages are never collapsed.

(5) Configurable fold threshold
    - AppState.foldThreshold (UserDefaults, default 8; was hardcoded 30).
    - WindowState.foldThreshold per-window mirror.
    - SettingsView.foldThresholdSection Picker (8 / 15 / 30 / Off).
    - WindowState.foldThreshold == 0 disables folding entirely.

(6) Focus Mode refresh
    - Removed the `if !windowState.focusMode` guard on StreamingMessageView.
    - Added a 50 ms throttled .task in MessageListView that calls
      rebuildSettledItems while streaming, so the settled list stays in
      sync with text-delta flushes.

(7) Visibility fix
    - MessageGroup in MessageListView relaxed from fileprivate to
      internal so PhaseGroupSummaryView can hold a MessageGroup typed
      property (compile error in Xcode toolchain).

(8) Project identity (MiniClarc v2.0.0)
    - CFBundleIdentifier: com.idealapp.Clarc -> com.dttxorg.MiniClarc.
    - CFBundleName: Clarc -> MiniClarc.
    - MARKETING_VERSION: 1.3.0 -> 2.0.0 (independent version line).
    - CURRENT_PROJECT_VERSION: 26 -> 1.
    - SUFeedURL: ttnear/Clarc/main/appcast.xml ->
      dttxorg/MiniClarc/main/appcast.xml.
    - SUPublicEDKey: cleared (was upstream ttnear's key; not reusable).
    - NSHumanReadableCopyright: filled in with Apache 2.0 attribution.
    - Settings → open-source panel now shows three links (this fork,
      upstream attribution, full LICENSE text).
    - README.md, FORK.md, this NOTICE rewritten for the new identity.

